Quote:  SUGGESTIONS FOR RESOURCES EQUAL TO DEFICIT FROM LOSS OF SUBSIDY.- 1st. The Government to compensate us for loss of subsidy by granting the licenses as annexed: Public houses L150; liquor, L100; .. 2nd. To relieve the Corporation of their debt incurred under the impression that the subsidy would be continued. This, with the Crown Grants for Oamaru Town Reserves, would enable the Coproration to contunue such works and improvements as were needed.
